<section>
  <h2>EEOC Complaint Checklist</h2>
  <p>
    Use this quick checklist to track your progress through the EEOC process. Each step includes what you’ll need and when to act.
  </p>

  <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; text-align: left; max-width: 600px; margin: 2em auto; background: #fff; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
    <li style="padding: 1em; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;">
      <input type="checkbox" id="step1">
      <label for="step1"><strong>1. File an EEOC Charge</strong> — Submit your charge online, by mail, or in person at your nearest EEOC office.</label>
    </li>
    <li style="padding: 1em; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;">
      <input type="checkbox" id="step2">
      <label for="step2"><strong>2. Provide Supporting Evidence</strong> — Include emails, notes, witness names, or documents to strengthen your claim.</label>
    </li>
    <li style="padding: 1em; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;">
      <input type="checkbox" id="step3">
      <label for="step3"><strong>3. Respond to Information Requests</strong> — Watch for EEOC communications and reply promptly to stay on track.</label>
    </li>
    <li style="padding: 1em; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;">
      <input type="checkbox" id="step4">
      <label for="step4"><strong>4. Participate in Mediation</strong> — If offered, mediation can resolve your case faster without a full investigation.</label>
    </li>
    <li